WorkItem.Description:
I added a delegate to Quality.cs for this:

    public delegate bool UserQualityTest( Mesh pMesher, Triangle pTriangle, double pArea );

(although I don't use the Mesh at the moment).

Also added to the Options enum:

     /// 
     /// Sets the usertest function for triangle quality
     /// 
     UserTest

And added SetOption support for that in Mesh.cs:

     public void SetOption( Options option, UserQualityTest func )
     {
         if( option == Options.UserTest )
         {
             behavior.Usertest = (func != null);
             quality.userTest = func;
         }
     }

Then, of course, it's just a case of changing Quality.cs to pass the correct arguments:

     if( userTest( mesh, testtri.triangle, area ) )

Hope this helps!
